window.bookSummaryJSON = "Blackstone Audio presents an eclectic mix of stories, plays and sketches dedicated to the thinking paranoiac. Gore, sex, horror, literature and edifying morals - what more could you want from an audiobook? <p>This collection includes \"In a Grove\", upon which Akira Kurosawa based his classic film, <i>Rashomon</i>; an adult fairy tale by the author of <i>Winnie-the-Pooh</i>; the real story (honest!) behind Edgar Rice Burroughs's novel <i>The Moon Maid</i>; and cautionary and scary tales from <i>The Arabian Nights</i>, Dostoevsky, Kafka, Mark Twain, and others. Selected, adapted, produced, and directed by Yuri Rasovsky.</p>"; 
